Node.js script to ingest Jira events:

```javascript
const JiraClient = require('jira-connector');
const client = new JiraClient({host: 'yourdomain.atlassian.net'});
client.issue.getIssue({issueKey: 'PROJ-123'}, function(error, issue) {
  saveToDataLake(issue);
});
```
